<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In ZF1.5 the following works:</p>

<p>$element-&gt;getValidator('Zend_Validate_StringLength');</p>

<p>in ZF1.6RC1 this returns false, the following must be used instead:</p>

<p>$element-&gt;getValidator('stringLength');</p>

<p>It seems to be related to a refactoring that changed the Validators to lazy-load, but the older syntax should be made to work.</p>

